A football group has provided a lifeline for people with Parkinson's disease. The weekly event, held at Solihull Walking Football Centre, gives members a chance to make new friends and improve their fitness. Footballers said they forgot all about their condition once they crossed the white line on a Monday morning. "It's just the best feeling in the world to be on the football pitch," said player Simon Forest.
